    "Ultimately, the output of the combination of radiologist plus the AI system must be optimized.",
    "These challenges can be further compounded by negative workplace attitudes [85] and factors that decrease personal perception of accountability [86] including radiologist burnout, and high workloads, both currently ubiquitous in radiology practice.A robust approach to mitigating biases and challenges related to reliance involves continuous radiologist education about AI capabilities and limitations.",
    "Providing comprehensive information about AI decision-making, its results, and confidence levels can enhance transparency and help radiologists make informed judgments.",
    "In addition, categorizing scenarios where AI assistance may falter, and integrating that information into a robust training program, can empower radiologists to recognize and rectify errors.",
